cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.ET, cs.SY, cs.SE

This paper proposes a new mechanism for improving the performance of phase-change memory (PCM) devices by enabling partition-level parallelism within each PCM bank. The paper focuses on the hardware implementation of PCM and proposes modifications to the PCM logic and interface. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.AR (Architecture), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.ET (Embedded Systems). The paper also discusses access scheduling mechanisms and power management, which are relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
